In case of AD, acetylcholine level decreases due to its hydrolysis through acetylcholinesterase enzyme in cholinergic and non-cholinergic neurons of the brain [39]. The improved AchE activity nearby amyloid plaques leads to the accumulation of amyloid beta peptides into fibrils and so rises plaques cytotoxicity. The result attained from the assay confirms that the ptGQD and DO-ptGQD have more % inhibition of AchE i.e. 79.65 ± 0.84 and 86.23 ± 1.28 respectively, as compared to the donepezil (72.46 ± 2.21) (Fig. 6
                               and Table 4
                              ). The results evidently indicates that the DO-ptGQD show greater percentage inhibition as compared to ptGQD as DO-ptGQD contains donepezil and the quantum dots prepared from Polygala tenuifolia, their combination provides synergistic effect to treat the alzheimer disease, as the plant Polygala tenuifolia is known to improve the learning and memory capacity.
